      "widgets_values": [
        "=== MIRA INPAINTING WORKFLOW ===\n\nHOW TO USE:\n1. Load your T-pose image in the 'Source Image' node\n2. RIGHT-CLICK the image → 'Open in MaskEditor'\n3. Paint WHITE over the area you want to fix (the leg)\n4. Click 'Save to node' in the mask editor\n5. Hit Queue Prompt\n\nTUNING:\n- Denoise 0.75: Good balance of change vs consistency\n  - Lower (0.5-0.6): Subtle fix, more original preserved\n  - Higher (0.8-1.0): More creative freedom, may drift\n- The prompt should match your original generation\n- Randomize noise seed to try different results\n\nThe mask is WHITE = inpaint, BLACK = keep original."
      ],
      "title": "Instructions"
    }
